=Generate technical audit questions in English based on the following deficiencies detected for the provider {{ $("Set Input Params").first().json.provider }}.

**IMPORTANT**: Each deficiency has an "id" field which is the requirement_id. You MUST include this requirement_id with each question you generate, linking the question back to its source deficiency.

DEFICIENCIES:
{{ JSON.stringify($json.total_deficiencies) }}

## PROJECT CONTEXT: {{ $('Fetch Project Context QA').first().json.ai_context }}

## DISCIPLINES:
{{ $('Fetch Project Context QA').first().json.disciplines ? 'Use ONLY these project-specific disciplines: ' + $('Fetch Project Context QA').first().json.disciplines.join(', ') : 'No disciplines defined yet for this project. You MUST first determine the appropriate engineering disciplines based on the project context and the deficiencies provided. Typical disciplines include: Electrical, Mechanical, Civil, Process, Instrumentation, Structural, Environmental, General, etc. Choose the ones that best fit this specific project.' }}

### INSTRUCTIONS:
1.  **Link to Requirement**: Each question MUST include the "requirement_id" (the "id" field from the deficiency it relates to).
2.  **Determine Disciplines**: First, identify the relevant engineering disciplines for THIS project based on the deficiencies and project context. Then classify each question into the most specific discipline.
    - Be as specific as possible. Do not label everything as "General".
    - Only use "General" if it is truly administrative or multi-disciplinary.
3.  **Language**: All questions and text MUST be in English.
4.  **Format**: Respond strictly with the JSON object following the schema.

### OUTPUT SCHEMA:
{
  "disciplines": ["list of all unique discipline names used in the questions below"],
  "questions": [
    {
      "requirement_id": "uuid-from-deficiency-id-field",
      "discipline": "One of the disciplines listed above",
      "question": "The specific question in English",
      "importance": "High" | "Medium" | "Low"
    }
  ]
}

parameters.jsCode:
// Extract unique disciplines from the QA Generation Chain output
// and merge with existing project disciplines
const qaOutput = $('QA Generation Chain').first().json.output || {};
const generatedDisciplines = qaOutput.disciplines || [];
const existingDisciplines = $('Fetch Project Context QA').first().json.disciplines || [];

// Merge: existing + new, deduplicated
const allDisciplines = [...new Set([...existingDisciplines, ...generatedDisciplines])];
const projectId = $('Set Input Params').first().json.project_id;

// Format as PostgreSQL array literal for safe Supabase handling
const pgArray = '{' + allDisciplines.map(d => '"' + d.replace(/"/g, '\\"') + '"').join(',') + '}';

console.log(`📋 Disciplines for project ${projectId}:`);
console.log(`   ├─ Existing: ${existingDisciplines.join(', ') || 'none'}`);
console.log(`   ├─ Generated: ${generatedDisciplines.join(', ')}`);
console.log(`   └─ Merged (${allDisciplines.length}): ${allDisciplines.join(', ')}`);

return [{ json: { project_id: projectId, disciplines: pgArray } }];

// =============================================
// NODO: Prepare Scoring Data (v5 - Dynamic Criteria Support)
// Supports both hardcoded defaults and dynamic criteria from database
// =============================================

const items = $input.all();

console.log('📊 Prepare Scoring Data - Starting...');
console.log('   Items received:', items.length);

/* =========================
Get project_id from webhook
========================= */
let projectId = null;
try {
    projectId = $('Set Input Params1').first().json.project_id;
    console.log('   📋 Project ID:', projectId);
} catch (e) {
    console.log('   ⚠️ Could not get project_id:', e.message);
}

/* =========================
Get Dynamic Scoring Configuration (if exists)
========================= */
let dynamicConfig = null;
let useDynamicConfig = false;
try {
    const configItems = $('Fetch Scoring Configuration').all();
    if (configItems && configItems.length > 0 && configItems[0].json.category_name) {
        // Parse configuration into structured format
        const configData = configItems.map(item => item.json);
        dynamicConfig = {
            categories: {},
            criteria: {},
            criteriaWeights: {},
            categoryWeights: {}
        };

        configData.forEach(row => {
            const catName = row.category_name;
            const catWeight = parseFloat(row.category_weight) || 0;

            if (!dynamicConfig.categories[catName]) {
                dynamicConfig.categories[catName] = {
                    name: catName,
                    display_name: row.category_display_name,
                    weight: catWeight,
                    color: row.category_color,
                    criteria: []
                };
                dynamicConfig.categoryWeights[catName.toUpperCase()] = catWeight / 100;
            }

            if (row.criterion_name) {
                const critName = row.criterion_name;
                const critWeight = parseFloat(row.criterion_weight) || 0;
                const actualWeight = (critWeight * catWeight) / 10000; // criterion_weight% of category_weight%

                dynamicConfig.criteria[critName] = {
                    name: critName,
                    display_name: row.criterion_display_name,
                    description: row.criterion_description,
                    category: catName,
                    weight: critWeight,
                    keywords: row.criterion_keywords || []
                };
                dynamicConfig.criteriaWeights[critName] = actualWeight;
                dynamicConfig.categories[catName].criteria.push(critName);
            }
        });

        useDynamicConfig = Object.keys(dynamicConfig.criteria).length > 0;
        console.log('   ✅ Dynamic configuration loaded:', Object.keys(dynamicConfig.criteria).length, 'criteria');
    }
} catch (e) {
    console.log('   ⚠️ Could not load dynamic config:', e.message);
}

/* =========================
Default Criteria (fallback)
========================= */
const DEFAULT_CRITERIA_WEIGHTS = {
    scope_facilities: 0.10,
    scope_work: 0.10,
    deliverables_quality: 0.10,
    total_price: 0.15,
    price_breakdown: 0.08,
    optionals_included: 0.07,
    capex_opex_methodology: 0.05,
    schedule: 0.08,
    resources_allocation: 0.06,
    exceptions: 0.06,
    safety_studies: 0.08,
    regulatory_compliance: 0.07
};

const DEFAULT_CATEGORY_WEIGHTS = {
    TECHNICAL: 0.30,
    ECONOMIC: 0.35,
    EXECUTION: 0.20,
    HSE_COMPLIANCE: 0.15
};

// Use dynamic or default
const CRITERIA_WEIGHTS = useDynamicConfig ? dynamicConfig.criteriaWeights : DEFAULT_CRITERIA_WEIGHTS;
const CATEGORY_WEIGHTS = useDynamicConfig ? dynamicConfig.categoryWeights : DEFAULT_CATEGORY_WEIGHTS;

console.log('   📊 Using', useDynamicConfig ? 'DYNAMIC' : 'DEFAULT', 'configuration');
console.log('   📊 Criteria:', Object.keys(CRITERIA_WEIGHTS).join(', '));

/* =========================
Helpers - Map requirements to criteria
========================= */
function getCriterionFromRequirement(evalType, phase, reqText, keywords) {
    const type = (evalType || '').toLowerCase();
    const phaseL = (phase || '').toLowerCase();
    const text = (reqText || '').toLowerCase();

    // If using dynamic config, try to match by keywords first
    if (useDynamicConfig && dynamicConfig.criteria) {
        for (const [critName, critInfo] of Object.entries(dynamicConfig.criteria)) {
            const kws = critInfo.keywords || [];
            for (const kw of kws) {
                if (text.includes(kw.toLowerCase())) {
                    return critName;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    // Fallback to default mapping logic
    if (type.includes('technical')) {
        if (text.includes('scope of facilities') || text.includes('hydrogen plant') || text.includes('utilities')) {
            return 'scope_facilities';
        }
        if (text.includes('scope of work') || text.includes('project management') || text.includes('deliverables')) {
            return 'scope_work';
        }
        if (text.includes('p&id') || text.includes('3d model') || text.includes('specification') || text.includes('datasheet')) {
            return 'deliverables_quality';
        }
        return 'scope_work';
    }

    if (type.includes('econom')) {
        if (text.includes('price') || text.includes('€') || text.includes('fee') || text.includes('cost')) {
            return 'total_price';
        }
        if (text.includes('hour') || text.includes('discipline') || text.includes('breakdown')) {
            return 'price_breakdown';
        }
        if (text.includes('optional') || text.includes('geotechnical') || text.includes('topograph') || text.includes('hazid')) {
            return 'optionals_included';
        }
        if (text.includes('capex') || text.includes('opex') || text.includes('aacei') || text.includes('estimate')) {
            return 'capex_opex_methodology';
        }
        return 'total_price';
    }

    if (text.includes('hse') || text.includes('safety') || text.includes('hazop') || text.includes('hazid') || text.includes('atex') || text.includes('qra')) {
        return 'safety_studies';
    }
    if (text.includes('code') || text.includes('standard') || text.includes('compliance') || text.includes('regulation')) {
        return 'regulatory_compliance';
    }

    if (phaseL.includes('pre-feed') || phaseL.includes('feed') || type.includes('deliverable')) {
        if (text.includes('schedule') || text.includes('planning') || text.includes('timeline')) {
            return 'schedule';
        }
        if (text.includes('exception') || text.includes('deviation') || text.includes('exclusion')) {
            return 'exceptions';
        }
        return 'resources_allocation';
    }

    return 'scope_work';
}

function classifyEval(val) {
    const v = (val || '').toUpperCase();
    if (v.includes('INCLUD') || v.includes('INCLUIDO') || v === 'SI' || v === 'YES') return 'INCLUDED';
    if (v.includes('PARCIAL') || v.includes('PARTIAL')) return 'PARTIAL';
    if (v.includes('NO INCLUD') || v.includes('NOT INCLUD') || v === 'NO') return 'NOT_INCLUDED';
    return 'NO_INFO';
}

/* =========================
Get data from previous nodes
========================= */
let requirements = [];
let responses = [];

try {
    const reqItems = $('Fetch Requirements').all();
    requirements = reqItems.map(item => item.json);
    console.log('   ✅ Requirements from Fetch Requirements:', requirements.length);
} catch (e) {
    console.log('   ⚠️ Could not access Fetch Requirements:', e.message);
}

try {
    const respItems = $('Fetch Provider Responses').all();
    responses = respItems.map(item => item.json);
    console.log('   ✅ Responses from Fetch Provider Responses:', responses.length);
} catch (e) {
    console.log('   ⚠️ Could not access Fetch Provider Responses:', e.message);
}

if (requirements.length === 0 || responses.length === 0) {
    console.log('   🔄 Using fallback: separating from input...');
    items.forEach(item => {
        const data = item.json;
        if (data.requirement_text && !data.provider_name) {
            requirements.push(data);
        } else if (data.provider_name && data.requirement_id) {
            responses.push(data);
        }
    });
}

if (requirements.length === 0) {
    return [{ json: { error: 'No requirements found', items_received: items.length } }];
}
if (responses.length === 0) {
    return [{ json: { error: 'No responses found', items_received: items.length } }];
}

/* =========================
Optimization with MAPS
========================= */
const requirementMap = {};
requirements.forEach(r => {
    if (r.id) requirementMap[r.id] = r;
});

const responsesByProvider = {};
responses.forEach(r => {
    if (r.provider_name) {
        if (!responsesByProvider[r.provider_name]) {
            responsesByProvider[r.provider_name] = [];
        }
        responsesByProvider[r.provider_name].push(r);
    }
});

console.log('   📊 Providers found:', Object.keys(responsesByProvider).join(', '));

/* =========================
Provider filter (optional)
========================= */
let providerFilter = '';
try {
    providerFilter = $('Set Input Params1').first().json.provider_filter || '';
} catch (e) {}

let providers = Object.keys(responsesByProvider);
if (providerFilter) {
    providers = providers.filter(p => p.toLowerCase().includes(providerFilter.toLowerCase()));
}

if (providers.length === 0) {
    return [{ json: { error: 'No providers found', filter: providerFilter } }];
}

/* =========================
Evaluation by Criteria
========================= */
const evaluationData = providers.map(providerName => {
    const providerResponses = responsesByProvider[providerName] || [];

    // Initialize criteria summary
    const criteriaScores = {};
    Object.keys(CRITERIA_WEIGHTS).forEach(criterion => {
        criteriaScores[criterion] = { total: 0, included: 0, partial: 0, not_included: 0, no_info: 0, scores: [] };
    });

    providerResponses.forEach(resp => {
        const req = requirementMap[resp.requirement_id];
        if (!req) return;

        const criterion = getCriterionFromRequirement(req.evaluation_type, req.phase, req.requirement_text);
        const evalClass = classifyEval(resp.evaluation_value);

        const cs = criteriaScores[criterion];
        if (!cs) return;

        cs.total++;
        if (evalClass === 'INCLUDED') cs.included++;
        else if (evalClass === 'PARTIAL') cs.partial++;
        else if (evalClass === 'NOT_INCLUDED') cs.not_included++;
        else cs.no_info++;

        if (typeof resp.score === 'number') {
            cs.scores.push(resp.score);
        }
    });

    // Calculate average scores per criterion
    let globalScore = 0;
    const criteriaAvgScores = {};

    Object.keys(criteriaScores).forEach(criterion => {
        const cs = criteriaScores[criterion];
        if (cs.scores.length > 0) {
            cs.avg_score = Math.round((cs.scores.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / cs.scores.length) * 100) / 100;
        } else if (cs.total > 0) {
            cs.avg_score = Math.round(((cs.included * 10 + cs.partial * 5) / cs.total) * 100) / 100;
        } else {
            cs.avg_score = 0;
        }
        criteriaAvgScores[criterion] = cs.avg_score;
        globalScore += cs.avg_score * (CRITERIA_WEIGHTS[criterion] || 0);
        delete cs.scores;
    });

    globalScore = Math.round(globalScore * 100) / 100;

    // Calculate category scores dynamically
    let categoryScores = {};
    if (useDynamicConfig) {
        for (const [catName, catInfo] of Object.entries(dynamicConfig.categories)) {
            const catCriteria = catInfo.criteria || [];
            const scores = catCriteria.map(c => criteriaAvgScores[c] || 0);
            const avg = scores.length > 0 ? scores.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / scores.length : 0;
            categoryScores[catName.toUpperCase()] = Math.round(avg * 100) / 100;
        }
    } else {
        categoryScores = {
            TECHNICAL: Math.round(((criteriaAvgScores.scope_facilities || 0) + (criteriaAvgScores.scope_work || 0) + (criteriaAvgScores.deliverables_quality || 0)) / 3 * 100) / 100,
            ECONOMIC: Math.round(((criteriaAvgScores.total_price || 0) + (criteriaAvgScores.price_breakdown || 0) + (criteriaAvgScores.optionals_included || 0) + (criteriaAvgScores.capex_opex_methodology || 0)) / 4 * 100) / 100,
            EXECUTION: Math.round(((criteriaAvgScores.schedule || 0) + (criteriaAvgScores.resources_allocation || 0) + (criteriaAvgScores.exceptions || 0)) / 3 * 100) / 100,
            HSE_COMPLIANCE: Math.round(((criteriaAvgScores.safety_studies || 0) + (criteriaAvgScores.regulatory_compliance || 0)) / 2 * 100) / 100
        };
    }

    return {
        provider_name: providerName,
        project_id: projectId,
        total_responses: providerResponses.length,
        global_score: globalScore,
        category_scores: categoryScores,
        criteria_scores: criteriaAvgScores,
        criteria_summary: criteriaScores,
        config_type: useDynamicConfig ? 'dynamic' : 'default',
        scoring_config: useDynamicConfig ? dynamicConfig : null
    };
});

/* =========================
Executive Ranking
========================= */
evaluationData
    .sort((a, b) => b.global_score - a.global_score)
    .forEach((item, index) => {
        item.rank = index + 1;
    });

console.log('✅ Scoring Data prepared for', evaluationData.length, 'providers');
console.log('   Project ID included:', projectId);
console.log('   Config type:', useDynamicConfig ? 'DYNAMIC' : 'DEFAULT');

return evaluationData.map(data => ({ json: data }));

parameters.text:
=Score this engineering proposal provider based on RFQ compliance.

## PROVIDER: {{ $json.provider_name }}
## TOTAL RESPONSES: {{ $json.total_responses }}
\n## PROJECT CONTEXT: {{ $('Fetch Project Context Scoring').first().json.ai_context }}\n\n## CONFIG TYPE: {{ $json.config_type || 'default' }}

## CATEGORY SCORES (pre-calculated):
{{ JSON.stringify($json.category_scores, null, 2) }}

## INDIVIDUAL CRITERIA SCORES:
{{ JSON.stringify($json.criteria_scores, null, 2) }}

## CRITERIA DETAILS:
{{ JSON.stringify($json.criteria_summary, null, 2) }}

{{ $json.scoring_config ? '## DYNAMIC SCORING CONFIGURATION:\n' + JSON.stringify($json.scoring_config.categories, null, 2) : '' }}

## EVALUATION CRITERIA (weights):
{{ $json.scoring_config ? Object.entries($json.scoring_config.categories).map(([name, cat]) => `### ${cat.display_name} (${cat.weight}%)\n${cat.criteria.map(c => `- ${c}: ${$json.scoring_config.criteria[c]?.description || ''}`).join('\n')}`).join('\n\n') : `### TECHNICAL COMPLETENESS (30%)
- scope_facilities: 10% - H2 plant, BOP, utilities included
- scope_work: 10% - PM, studies, deliverables covered
- deliverables_quality: 10% - P&IDs, specs, 3D model quality

### ECONOMIC COMPETITIVENESS (35%)
- total_price: 15% - PRE-FEED + FEED + EPC price competitiveness
- price_breakdown: 8% - Transparent hours/discipline, €/hour
- optionals_included: 7% - Geotechnical, topographic, 3D, HAZID in base
- capex_opex_methodology: 5% - AACEI class, estimate robustness

### EXECUTION CAPABILITY (20%)
- schedule: 8% - Realistic timeline vs requirements
- resources_allocation: 6% - Coherent hours per discipline
- exceptions: 6% - Fewer exceptions = better (invert score)

### HSE & COMPLIANCE (15%)
- safety_studies: 8% - HAZID, HAZOP, QRA, ATEX included
- regulatory_compliance: 7% - Codes, standards, safety distances` }}

## SCORING RULES:
- included items = 10 points
- partial items = 6 points
- not_included items = 2 points
- no_info items = 0 points
- For 'exceptions': FEWER is BETTER (invert: more exceptions = lower score)

## OUTPUT (JSON only):
