## /qa-process-email-response - AI Email Response Mapper

Processes supplier email responses and maps them to original Q&A questions using AI.

**Method**: POST
**Body**: { project_id, provider_name, email_content }

**Flow**: Webhook → Set Fields → Fetch Q&A Questions → Build AI Context → LLM Chain → Parse Output → Respond

**Returns**: { success, processed_count, mappings: [{ question_id, question_text, response_text, confidence, matched }] }

parameters.jsCode:
// Build context for LLM: combine Q&A questions with email content
const questions = $('Fetch QA Questions').all();
const params = $('Set QA Email Params').first().json;

const questionList = questions.map(q => ({
  id: q.json.id,
  question: q.json.question,
  discipline: q.json.discipline,
  importance: q.json.importance,
  status: q.json.status
}));

console.log(`📧 Processing email response:`);
console.log(`   ├─ Provider: ${params.provider_name}`);
console.log(`   ├─ Questions found: ${questionList.length}`);
console.log(`   └─ Email length: ${(params.email_content || '').length} chars`);

return [{
  json: {
    project_id: params.project_id,
    provider_name: params.provider_name,
    email_content: params.email_content,
    questions: questionList,
    total_questions: questionList.length
  }
}];

parameters.text:
=### INPUT

## PROVIDER: {{ $json.provider_name }}

## ORIGINAL QUESTIONS ({{ $json.total_questions }} items):
{{ JSON.stringify($json.questions, null, 2) }}

## SUPPLIER EMAIL RESPONSE:
{{ $json.email_content }}

### INSTRUCTIONS
Analyze the supplier's email response and map each answer to its most likely original question.
For each mapping, provide a confidence score (0.0 to 1.0) indicating how certain you are of the match.
If a question has no corresponding answer in the email, set matched=false and response_text to empty string.

Return ONLY the JSON object. Do NOT include any text before or after the JSON.

### OUTPUT SCHEMA
{
  "success": true,
  "processed_count": <number of matched responses>,
  "mappings": [
    {
      "question_id": "<uuid from original question>",
      "question_text": "<original question text>",
      "response_text": "<extracted response from email>",
      "confidence": <0.0 to 1.0>,
      "matched": <true/false>
    }
  ]
}

parameters.jsCode:
// Parse LLM output and ensure correct response format
const llmOutput = $input.first().json;
let result;

try {
  // The LLM chain returns output in .text or .output
  const rawText = llmOutput.text || llmOutput.output || JSON.stringify(llmOutput);

  // Try to parse as JSON
  let parsed;
  if (typeof rawText === 'string') {
    // Clean potential markdown code blocks
    const cleaned = rawText.replace(/```json\n?/g, '').replace(/```\n?/g, '').trim();
    parsed = JSON.parse(cleaned);
  } else {
    parsed = rawText;
  }

  // Validate and normalize
  const mappings = (parsed.mappings || []).map(m => ({
    question_id: m.question_id || '',
    question_text: m.question_text || '',
    response_text: m.response_text || '',
    confidence: typeof m.confidence === 'number' ? m.confidence : 0,
    matched: m.matched === true
  }));

  const matchedCount = mappings.filter(m => m.matched).length;

  result = {
    success: true,
    processed_count: matchedCount,
    mappings: mappings,
    message: `Processed ${matchedCount} of ${mappings.length} questions from email`
  };

  console.log(`✅ QA Email Response processed:`);
  console.log(`   ├─ Total mappings: ${mappings.length}`);
  console.log(`   └─ Matched: ${matchedCount}`);
} catch (err) {
  console.error('❌ Error parsing LLM output:', err.message);
  result = {
    success: false,
    processed_count: 0,
    mappings: [],
    message: 'Error parsing AI response: ' + err.message
  };
}

return [{ json: result }];

parameters.content:
## /rfp-generate - AI RFP Document Generator

Generates a complete RFP/RFQ/RFI document using AI based on project requirements.

**Method**: POST
**Body**: { project_id, project_name, project_type, description, requirements, providers?, criteria?, deadlines?, language?, sections? }

**Flow**: Webhook → Set Fields → LLM Chain → Parse & Structure Output → Respond

**Returns**: { success, document, title, sections: [{title, content}], metadata: {word_count, generated_at, model} }

parameters.text:
=### INPUT

## PROJECT: {{ $json.project_name }}
## TYPE: {{ $json.project_type }}
## LANGUAGE: {{ $json.language }}

## DESCRIPTION:
{{ $json.description }}

## REQUIREMENTS:
{{ $json.requirements }}

## SECTIONS TO INCLUDE:
{{ JSON.stringify($json.sections) }}

## EVALUATION CRITERIA:
{{ JSON.stringify($json.criteria) }}

## DEADLINES:
{{ JSON.stringify($json.deadlines) }}

## INVITED PROVIDERS:
{{ JSON.stringify($json.providers) }}

### INSTRUCTIONS
Generate a complete, professional {{ $json.project_type }} document with ALL the requested sections.
The document must be in {{ $json.language === 'en' ? 'English' : 'Spanish' }}.
Use Markdown formatting for the document body.
Each section should be comprehensive and detailed.
Include the evaluation criteria and deadlines in the appropriate sections.

Return ONLY the JSON object. Do NOT include any text before or after the JSON.

### OUTPUT SCHEMA
{
  "title": "Document title",
  "document": "Full document content in Markdown",
  "sections": [
    { "title": "Section Name", "content": "Section content in Markdown" }
  ]
}

parameters.jsCode:
// Parse LLM output and structure the RFP response
const llmOutput = $input.first().json;
const params = $('Set RFP Params').first().json;
let result;

try {
  const rawText = llmOutput.text || llmOutput.output || JSON.stringify(llmOutput);

  let parsed;
  if (typeof rawText === 'string') {
    const cleaned = rawText.replace(/```json\n?/g, '').replace(/```\n?/g, '').trim();
    parsed = JSON.parse(cleaned);
  } else {
    parsed = rawText;
  }

  // Build sections array
  const sections = (parsed.sections || []).map(s => ({
    title: s.title || 'Untitled Section',
    content: s.content || ''
  }));

  // Build full document
  const document = parsed.document || sections.map(s => `## ${s.title}\n\n${s.content}`).join('\n\n');

  // Calculate word count
  const wordCount = document.split(/\s+/).filter(w => w.length > 0).length;

  result = {
    success: true,
    title: parsed.title || `${params.project_type} - ${params.project_name}`,
    document: document,
    sections: sections,
    metadata: {
      word_count: wordCount,
      generated_at: new Date().toISOString(),
      model: 'mistral-large-latest'
    },
    message: `RFP generated successfully (${wordCount} words, ${sections.length} sections)`
  };

  console.log(`✅ RFP Generated:`);
  console.log(`   ├─ Title: ${result.title}`);
  console.log(`   ├─ Sections: ${sections.length}`);
  console.log(`   └─ Words: ${wordCount}`);
} catch (err) {
  console.error('❌ Error parsing RFP output:', err.message);
  result = {
    success: false,
    title: '',
    document: '',
    sections: [],
    metadata: { word_count: 0, generated_at: new Date().toISOString(), model: 'mistral-large-latest' },
    message: 'Error generating RFP: ' + err.message
  };
}

return [{ json: result }];

// =============================================
// NODE: Check If Economic Offer
// Determines if this supplier proposal contains economic/pricing data
// and prepares text for LLM extraction.
// =============================================

// Get the merged proposal data
const mergeData = $input.first().json;

// Get metadata from Set File ID
let providerName = 'UNKNOWN';
let projectId = null;
let projectName = '';
let evaluationTypes = [];

try {
    const fileData = $('Set File ID').first().json;
    providerName = fileData.proveedor || 'UNKNOWN';
    projectId = fileData.project_id || null;
    projectName = fileData.proyect_name || '';

    if (fileData.evaluation && Array.isArray(fileData.evaluation)) {
        evaluationTypes = fileData.evaluation;
    } else if (fileData.evaluation && typeof fileData.evaluation === 'string') {
        evaluationTypes = [fileData.evaluation];
    }
} catch (e) {
    console.log('Warning: Could not read Set File ID:', e.message);
}

// Check if evaluation types include economic
const hasEconomic = evaluationTypes.some(t => 
    t.toLowerCase().includes('econom') || 
    t.toLowerCase().includes('commercial') ||
    t.toLowerCase().includes('pricing')
);

// Also check text content for economic indicators as fallback
let fullText = '';
try {
    if (mergeData.pages && Array.isArray(mergeData.pages)) {
        fullText = mergeData.pages.map(p => p.text || '').join('\n\n');
    } else {
        fullText = mergeData.text || '';
    }
} catch (e) {
    fullText = '';
}

// Economic indicators in text
const economicKeywords = ['total price', 'precio total', 'price breakdown', 'desglose', 
    'payment terms', 'condiciones de pago', 'discount', 'descuento', 'EUR/h', 'USD/h',
    'lump sum', 'suma alzada', 'cost estimate', 'presupuesto', 'budget',
    'fee schedule', 'tarifa', 'quotation', 'cotizacion', 'oferta economica',
    'commercial proposal', 'propuesta economica', 'pricing schedule'];

const textLower = fullText.substring(0, 50000).toLowerCase();
const textHasEconomic = economicKeywords.some(kw => textLower.includes(kw));

const shouldExtract = hasEconomic || textHasEconomic;

console.log(`Economic Check:`);
console.log(`  Provider: ${providerName}`);
console.log(`  Project ID: ${projectId}`);
console.log(`  Eval types: ${JSON.stringify(evaluationTypes)}`);
console.log(`  Has economic type: ${hasEconomic}`);
console.log(`  Text has economic keywords: ${textHasEconomic}`);
console.log(`  Should extract: ${shouldExtract}`);

if (!shouldExtract) {
    console.log('Skipping economic extraction - no economic content detected');
    return [];
}

// Limit text to ~60k chars for LLM context
const textForExtraction = fullText.substring(0, 60000);

return [{
    json: {
        provider_name: providerName,
        project_id: projectId,
        project_name: projectName,
        proposal_text: textForExtraction,
        text_length: fullText.length,
        evaluation_types: evaluationTypes
    }
}];

// =============================================
// NODE: Parse Economic JSON
// Parses and validates the LLM economic extraction output
// =============================================

const llmOutput = $input.first().json;
const inputData = $('Check If Economic Offer').first().json;

let parsed = null;

try {
    // The LLM chain returns output in .text or .output
    let rawText = llmOutput.text || llmOutput.output || JSON.stringify(llmOutput);

    if (typeof rawText === 'string') {
        // Clean potential markdown code blocks
        rawText = rawText.replace(/```json\n?/g, '').replace(/```\n?/g, '').trim();

        // Find JSON boundaries
        const start = rawText.indexOf('{');
        const end = rawText.lastIndexOf('}');
        if (start !== -1 && end !== -1 && end > start) {
            rawText = rawText.substring(start, end + 1);
        }

        parsed = JSON.parse(rawText);
    } else {
        parsed = rawText;
    }
} catch (err) {
    console.error('Error parsing economic JSON:', err.message);
    // Return minimal valid record so we still save something
    parsed = {
        total_price: null,
        currency: 'EUR',
        extraction_confidence: 0.0,
        raw_notes: 'LLM output could not be parsed: ' + err.message
    };
}

// Helper to safely convert to number
function toNumber(val) {
    if (val === null || val === undefined) return null;
    if (typeof val === 'number') return val;
    if (typeof val === 'string') {
        // Remove currency symbols, commas, spaces
        const cleaned = val.replace(/[^0-9.-]/g, '');
        const num = parseFloat(cleaned);
        return isNaN(num) ? null : num;
    }
    return null;
}

// Helper to safely convert to JSON string for Supabase JSONB columns
function toJsonString(val) {
    if (val === null || val === undefined) return null;
    if (typeof val === 'string') return val;
    return JSON.stringify(val);
}

// Build the record for Supabase
const record = {
    project_id: inputData.project_id,
    provider_name: inputData.provider_name,

    // Core pricing
    total_price: toNumber(parsed.total_price),
    currency: parsed.currency || 'EUR',
    price_breakdown: toJsonString(parsed.price_breakdown || {}),

    // Payment terms
    payment_terms: parsed.payment_terms || null,
    payment_schedule: toJsonString(parsed.payment_schedule || []),

    // Discounts
    discount_percentage: toNumber(parsed.discount_percentage) || 0,
    discount_conditions: parsed.discount_conditions || null,

    // TCO
    tco_value: toNumber(parsed.tco_value),
    tco_period_years: parsed.tco_period_years ? parseInt(parsed.tco_period_years) : null,
    tco_breakdown: toJsonString(parsed.tco_breakdown || {}),

    // Additional
    validity_days: parsed.validity_days ? parseInt(parsed.validity_days) : 90,
    price_escalation: parsed.price_escalation || null,
    guarantees: parsed.guarantees || null,
    insurance_included: parsed.insurance_included === true,
    taxes_included: parsed.taxes_included === true,

    // Optional / alternatives
    optional_items: toJsonString(parsed.optional_items || []),
    alternative_offers: toJsonString(parsed.alternative_offers || []),

    // AI metadata
    extraction_confidence: toNumber(parsed.extraction_confidence) || 0,
    raw_notes: parsed.raw_notes || null
};

console.log('Economic data parsed successfully:');
console.log(`  Provider: ${record.provider_name}`);
console.log(`  Total price: ${record.total_price} ${record.currency}`);
console.log(`  Confidence: ${record.extraction_confidence}`);
console.log(`  Has breakdown: ${record.price_breakdown !== '{}'}`);
console.log(`  Has payment terms: ${!!record.payment_terms}`);

// Validate: skip save if no project_id or provider_name
if (!record.project_id || !record.provider_name || record.provider_name === 'UNKNOWN') {
    console.log('WARNING: Missing project_id or provider_name, skipping save');
    return [];
}

return [{ json: record }];
